data.title: Great Food and  Very Nice People
data.text: This is a place where you can get a good meal and watch all kinds of sports. Every morning they clean each table top. Too bad some of the customer are slobs and make a mess. Yes there is peanut shells  all over the floor hence the name the Nutt House. if you don't like peanuts than don't come in. They make a great Steak sandwitch and awsome Cheese Burgers. and the burritoes are good too, Nacho's de Carne asada very, very good. um um ummmm good.

data.title: Dirty place,  bad food, many TV screens
data.text: This is a place to go and watch sports - the place is really dirty and the  tables are gross; the peanut shells on the floor have not been swept in days. The free peanuts are too old  and rancid, the food it truly terrible. We ordered quesedilla and a burrito to go with the beer - the food is so bad, it is not edible. The only reason one can go there is to take advantage of the many sports shown on multiple TV screens. But then, there are better and more sanitary ways to do watch sports.

data.title: Fun little hole-in-the wall place to go.  Good mexican food.  It's co-located with a great peanuts-on-the-floor...
data.text: Fun little hole-in-the wall place to go.  Good mexican food.  It's co-located with a great peanuts-on-the-floor neighborhood bar, the Nut House.  It's not for everybody, but I like it.
